"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:10.5.1\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">10.5.1</span> Earring, nose ring</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">נֶזֶם</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(nezem)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:22\">GEN 24:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:30\">GEN 24:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:47\">GEN 24:47</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:4\">GEN 35:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:2\">EXO 32:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:3\">EXO 32:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:22\">EXO 35:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:24\">JDG 8:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:24\">JDG 8:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:25\">JDG 8:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:26\">JDG 8:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:11\">JOB 42:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:22\">PRO 11:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:12\">PRO 25:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:21\">ISA 3:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:12\">EZK 16:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:15\">HOS 2:15</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">עָגִיל</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(‘agil)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num31:50\">NUM 31:50</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:12\">EZK 16:12</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">ἐνώτιον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(enōtion)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jdt10:4\">JDT 10:4</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description and usage:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0531_earrings_gold.jpg\" alt=\"Gold earrings\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">Gold earrings (Metropolitan Museum of Art, Public domain, MMA)</figcaption></figure>The earring was worn on the ear and the nose ring in the nose for decoration. They were small rings, usually made of silver or gold. They could have more or less elaborate decorative work attached to them.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>The Hebrew word <em>nezem</em> refers to a ring that could be worn in the ear or in the nose. In either case, it was worn as decorative jewelry.</p>\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/UBS-0037_nose_ring.jpg\" alt=\"Nose rings\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">Nose rings (© Deutsche Bibelgesellschaft, Stuttgart by United Bible Societies)</figcaption></figure>The Hebrew word <em>‘agil</em> in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:12\">EZK 16:12</a> clearly refers to an earring, and this is probably the case in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num31:50\">NUM 31:50</a> also.</p>\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/OAI-0071_head_of_woman_with_earrings.png\" alt=\"\n            \"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">\n             (Image generated by ChatGPT using OpenAI technology)</figcaption></figure>The Greek word <em>enōtion</em> in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jdt10:4\">JDT 10:4</a> specifically indicates a ring worn in the ear, not in the nose.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
